When the day and night have equal length, happens when the perpendicular projection of earth's axis on the ecliptic is tangential to the path drawn by the centre of the Earth on the ecliptic. There are two of them:

* *vernal* equinox, 21st of March (12 [RA](right ascension))
* *autumnal* equinox, 21st of September (0 RA)